The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Association under tax scanner
                                                                                                                       7                                      Association under tax scanner
            A STAFF REPORTER                      
	Calcutta: The officials of the service tax department of the Union ministry of finance visited the Cricket Association of Bengal (CAB) office, at Eden Gardens, on Friday.         
	It was learnt from sources that the officials questioned CABs accountant Dilip Chakraborty whether the state association has deposited the necessary service tax amounts from the revenue generated through organisation of Indian Premier League (IPL) matches.         
	Meanwhile, the Income-Tax department has instructed the state association to send one of their representatives for some further enquiry regarding the IPL tax related case.         
	It was learnt that senior official and former CAB joint secretary Chitrak Mitra might represent CAB.                                                                                                                     
